    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>A type of push dagger from the Indian subcontinent, characterised by an H-shaped hand grip that is perpendicular in relation to the blade. Ceremonial katars were also used in worship.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
